an class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>), <span class=\"fn\">⨆ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <span class=\"fn\">↑<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#NNNorm.nnnorm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#NNNorm.nnnorm\">‖₊</a></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">⨆ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <span class=\"fn\">↑<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#NNNorm.nnnorm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#NNNorm.nnnorm\">‖₊</a></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"This version of Banach-Steinhaus is stated in terms of suprema of `↑‖·‖₊ : ℝ≥0∞`\nfor convenience. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Operator/BanachSteinhaus.html#banach_steinhaus_iSup_nnnorm","kind":"theorem","line":44,"name":"banach_steinhaus_iSup_nnnorm","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Operator/BanachSteinhaus.lean#L44-L50"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Operator/BanachSteinhaus.html#banach_steinhaus\"><span class=\"name\">banach_steinhaus</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜₂</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#SeminormedAddCommGroup\">SeminormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#SeminormedAddCommGroup\">SeminormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Field/Basic.html#NontriviallyNormedField\">NontriviallyNormedField</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Field/Basic.html#NontriviallyNormedField\">NontriviallyNormedField</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜₂</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">σ₁₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Hom/Defs.html#RingHom\">→+*</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜₂</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Ring/Basic.html#RingHomIsometric\">RingHomIsometric</a> <span class=\"fn\">σ₁₂</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_5}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/Cauchy.html#CompleteSpace\">CompleteSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">g</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">ι</span> → <span class=\"fn\">E</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Module/LinearMap.html#ContinuousLinearMap\">→SL[</a><span class=\"fn\">σ₁₂</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/Module/LinearMap.html#ContinuousLinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>), <span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>), <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">C'</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>), <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">ι</span>), <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">C'</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"This is the standard Banach-Steinhaus theorem, or Uniform Boundedness Principle.\nIf a family of continuous linear maps from a Banach space into a normed space is pointwise\nbounded, then the norms of these linear maps are uniformly bounded.\n\nSee also `WithSeminorms.banach_steinhaus` for the general statement in barrelled spaces. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Operator/BanachSteinhaus.html#banach_steinhaus","kind":"theorem","line":31,"name":"banach_steinhaus","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Operator/BanachSteinhaus.lean#L31-L40"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.Normed.Operator.NormedSpace","Mathlib.Analysis.LocallyConvex.Barrelled","Mathlib.Topology.Baire.CompleteMetrizable"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Analysis.Normed.Operator.BanachSteinhaus"}